The paper deals with the problem of adapting a crowd counting model to a specific camera scene with only a few labeled images. This problem is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves training a model to learn from limited data and adapt to new scenes. The paper also mentions the use of meta-learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the problem of crowd counting is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) applications.
